Weekly manifest generation on first Friday merge (GitHub Actions)

Overview
- Trigger the manifest generator only when a pull request is merged into the default branch, only on Fridays, and only once per Friday (first merge).
- Uses a sentinel git tag per date to ensure subsequent Friday merges do not run again.

Instructions
1) Create a workflow file at .github/workflows/manifest-weekly.yml in this repository.
2) Paste the following workflow contents and adjust the target branch name (master vs main) if needed.
3) Commit the workflow to the default branch.

Example workflow (manifest-weekly.yml)
```yaml
name: Weekly manifest on first Friday merge

on:
  pull_request:
    types: [closed]
    branches: [master]   # change to main if needed

permissions:
  contents: write

jobs:
  build-manifest:
    if: github.event.pull_request.merged == true
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
        with:
          fetch-depth: 0

      # Optional: set timezone if you don't want UTC
      - name: Check Friday and sentinel
        id: gate
        run: |
          DOW=$(date -u +%u)  # 5 == Friday (UTC)
          if [ "$DOW" != "5" ]; then
            echo "run=false" >> "$GITHUB_OUTPUT"
            exit 0
          fi
          git fetch --tags --force
          TAG="manifest-$(date -u +%Y-%m-%d)"
          if git rev-parse -q --verify "refs/tags/$TAG" >/dev/null; then
            echo "run=false" >> "$GITHUB_OUTPUT"
          else
            echo "run=true" >> "$GITHUB_OUTPUT"
            echo "tag=$TAG" >> "$GITHUB_OUTPUT"
          fi

      - name: Set up Python
        if: steps.gate.outputs.run == 'true'
        uses: actions/setup-python@v5
        with:
          python-version: '3.x'

      - name: Generate manifest
        if: steps.gate.outputs.run == 'true'
        run: python3 "scripts/manifest generator.py"

      - name: Commit and push manifest
        if: steps.gate.outputs.run == 'true'
        run: |
          git config user.name  "github-actions[bot]"
          git config user.email "41898282+github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com"
          git add site/sfguides/src/_shared_assets/quickstart-manifest.json
          git commit -m "chore(manifest): weekly refresh (first Friday merge)"
          git push

      - name: Create sentinel tag
        if: steps.gate.outputs.run == 'true'
        run: |
          git tag "${{ steps.gate.outputs.tag }}"
          git push origin "${{ steps.gate.outputs.tag }}"
```

Notes
- Change branches: [master] to [main] if your default branch is main.
- Timezone: The check uses UTC (date -u). To use a different timezone, export TZ before computing DOW or use a setup step to set the timezone.
- Idempotency: The manifest-YYYY-MM-DD tag prevents multiple runs on the same Friday.
- Requirements: The job needs permissions: contents: write to push the updated manifest and create the tag.
- Git history: actions/checkout@v4 with fetch-depth: 0 is required for tags and for the generator to read git history for lastUpdatedAt.


